UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1299
1 AN ACT relating to the operation of a motor vehicle.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 189.340 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) The driver of a vehicle overtaking other vehicles proceeding in the same direction
5 shall pass to the left of them and shall not again drive to the right until reasonably
6 clear of those vehicles. The driver of a vehicle overtaking streetcars may pass either
7 to the right or left when so directed by a police officer, when on a one (1) way street
8 or where the location of the tracks prevents compliance with this section, with
9 regard for other traffic.
10 (2) (a) The driver of a vehicle overtaking a bicycle or electric low-speed scooter
11 proceeding in the same direction shall:
12 1. If there is more than one (1) lane for traffic proceeding in the same
13 direction, move the vehicle to the immediate left, if the lane is available
14 and moving in the lane is reasonably safe; or
15 2. If there is only one (1) lane for traffic proceeding in the same direction,
16 pass to the left of the bicycle or electric low-speed scooter at a distance
17 of not less than three (3) feet between any portion of the vehicle and the
18 bicycle or electric low-speed scooter and maintain that distance until
19 safely past the overtaken bicycle or electric low-speed scooter. If space
20 on the roadway is not available to have a minimum distance of three (3)
21 feet between the vehicle and the bicycle or electric low-speed scooter,
22 then the driver of the passing vehicle shall use reasonable caution in
23 passing the bicyclist or electric low-speed scooter operator.
24 (b) The driver of a motor vehicle may drive to the left of the center of a roadway,
25 including when a no-passing zone is marked in accordance with subsection
26 (6) of this section, to pass a person operating a bicycle or electric low-speed
27 scooter only if the roadway to the left of the center is unobstructed for a
Page 1 of 12
XXXX 12/5/2025 1:38 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1299
1 sufficient distance to permit the driver to pass the person operating the bicycle
2 or electric low-speed scooter safely and avoid interference with oncoming
3 traffic. This paragraph does not authorize driving on the left side of the center
4 of the roadway when otherwise prohibited under state law.
5 (c) The operator of a bicycle or electric low-speed scooter shall not ride more
6 than two (2) abreast on a single highway lane unless operating on any part of
7 the roadway marked exclusively for bicycle use. Persons riding two (2)
8 abreast shall not impede the normal and reasonable movement of traffic.
9 (3) The operator of a vehicle may overtake and pass upon the right of another vehicle
10 only under the following conditions:
11 (a) When the vehicle overtaken is making or about to make a left turn; or
12 (b) Upon a roadway with unobstructed pavement of sufficient width for two (2)
13 or more lines of vehicles moving lawfully in the direction being traveled by
14 the overtaking vehicle.
15 (4) The operator of a vehicle may overtake and pass another vehicle upon the right only
16 under conditions permitting the passing in safety, and not by driving off the
17 roadway unless the vehicle being passed is at a complete stop and the passing may
18 be made safely.
19 (5) A person shall not drive a vehicle to the left side of the center of the roadway in
20 overtaking and passing another vehicle proceeding in the same direction unless the
21 left side is clearly visible and free of oncoming traffic for a sufficient distance
22 ahead to permit overtaking and passing to be completely made without interfering
23 with the safe operation of any vehicle approaching from the opposite direction or
24 any vehicle overtaken. In every event, the overtaking vehicle must return to the
25 right-hand side of the roadway before coming within two hundred (200) feet of any
26 vehicle approaching from the opposite direction.
27 (6) The commissioner of highways is hereby authorized to determine those portions of
Page 2 of 12
XXXX 12/5/2025 1:38 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1299
1 any highway where overtaking and passing or driving to the left of the roadway
2 would be especially hazardous and may by appropriate signs or markings on the
3 roadway indicate the beginning and end of the zones, and when signs or markings
4 are in place and clearly visible to an ordinarily observant person, every driver of a
5 vehicle shall obey the directions thereof, except as provided for in subsection (2)(b)
6 of this section.
7 (7) Whenever any roadway has been divided into three (3) or more clearly marked
8 lanes for travel in one (1) direction, the following additional rules shall apply:
9 (a) A person shall drive a vehicle as nearly as may be practical entirely within a
10 single lane and shall not move from that lane until the driver ascertains that
11 the movement can be made with safety;
12 (b) A person shall not drive a vehicle in the center lane except when overtaking
13 and passing another vehicle where the roadway is clearly visible and the
14 center lane is clear of traffic within a safe distance, or in preparation for a left
15 turn or where a center lane is at the time allocated exclusively to traffic
16 moving in the direction in which the vehicle is proceeding and is signposted
17 to give notice of the allocation;
18 (c) A person shall not operate a truck tractor, trailer, or semitrailer in the leftmost
19 lane except when entering or leaving a highway, yielding to traffic coming
20 onto the highway, or when traffic conditions exist which would prohibit safe
21 use of the right or center lanes; and
22 (d) Official signs may be erected directing slow-moving traffic to use a
23 designated lane or allocating specified lanes to traffic moving in the same
24 direction and operators of vehicles shall obey the directions of these signs.
25 (8) On any[ limited access] highway of four (4) lanes or more[ with a posted speed
26 limit of at least sixty-five (65) miles per hour], a person shall not operate a motor
27 vehicle in the leftmost lane at a speed lower than the posted speed limit, except
Page 3 of 12
XXXX 12/5/2025 1:38 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1299
1 when:
2 (a) Overtaking a slower vehicle;
3 (b) Yielding to traffic coming onto the highway;[ or]
4 (c) Preparing to make a left turn at an intersection or into a private drive or
5 roadway; or
6 (d) Traffic or road conditions exist which would prohibit safe use of the right or
7 center lanes.
8 (9) (a) Except as provided in paragraph (c) of this subsection, the operator of a motor
9 vehicle shall not follow another vehicle more closely than is reasonable and
10 prudent, having regard for the speed of the vehicle and the traffic upon and
11 condition of the highway.
12 (b) Except as provided in paragraph (c) of this subsection, the operator of any
13 motor truck, semitrailer truck, bus, or heavy construction equipment unit,
14 when traveling upon a highway outside of a business or residential district,
15 shall not follow within two hundred fifty (250) feet of another vehicle or
16 equipment unit. This subsection shall not prevent overtaking and passing, nor
17 shall it apply to any lane specially designated for use of motor trucks or
18 semitrailer trucks, buses or heavy construction equipment units.
19 (c) Paragraphs (a) and (b) of this subsection shall not apply to a trailing
20 commercial motor vehicle involved in a platoon as defined in KRS 281.010,
21 but shall apply to the commercial motor vehicle leading a platoon.
22 Section 2. KRS 189.990 is amended to read as follows:
