15 (2) (a) 1. Except as provided in subparagraph 2. of this paragraph, any person
16 who violates the weight provisions of KRS 189.212, 189.221, 189.222,
17 189.226, 189.230, 189.270, or 189.2713 shall be fined two cents ($0.02)
18 per pound for each pound of excess load when the excess is five
19 thousand (5,000) pounds or less. When the excess exceeds five thousand
20 (5,000) pounds the fine shall be two cents ($0.02) per pound for each
21 pound of excess load, but the fine levied shall not be less than one
22 hundred dollars ($100) and shall not be more than five hundred dollars
23 ($500).
24 2. Any person who violates a posted bridge weight limit on a state-
25 maintained bridge that is more than seventy-five (75) years old shall be
26 fined:
27 a. Five hundred dollars ($500) for the first offense;
